<font color="#FF0000">MY THOUGHTS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jun 12  1:18:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all,<br>
I guess that time really heals MANY wounds (notice I did not say ALL wounds).  I do give credit to the Vietnamese people for enduring a century of struggle.  My question is this:  Are the Vietnamese people more forgiving or are they seeking a type of healing and peace that comes with sitting down with former enemies, visiting battle sites and discussing the events that forever changed the youth of both Asian and America?<br>
I don't believe the Vietnamese are more forgiving, remember we helped build Japan and Germany after the war and now both are economic as well as military allies (Pretty big task).  Besides can anyone really ever forgive the events of any war or can they come to understand them and learn from them.  I do believe the Vietnamese people seek a understanding to the events that enveloped their country for so long and Americans seek a understanding for a horrible war that divided this nation.  <br><br>
I do believe the current Communist Vietnamese is open to former enemies so that they can get economic aid for their country though.  In some ways it is confusing to me, the Vietnamese government still releases propoganda calling us imperialists, yet would accept money and any assistance from us.  I guess I'm trying to understand that.  <br><br>
I'm glad that former enemies as well as allies are able to sit down now and talk on a person to person level, if not on a government to government level.  I believe the average Vietnamese and the average American have more in common then they ever believed before.  It is not easy for a American to go back to Vietnam and I imagine it is not easy for a Vietnamese to have Americans back, but I give much credit to all for trying and keeping the lines of communication open.      <br>
Open dialog is the most important thing in this world (in marriage and in friendship), and all the pain and joy that goes with talking is in a way worth it.<br><br>
Many of us (Vets, protestors, objectors, Vietnamese, Amerasians, students or children of Nam vets) may never get to go to Vietnam or return there (I would like to go someday to see Vietnam), but at least we have a dialog here.  So lets do our best to keep talking here and to anyone who will listen.<br>
Peace to all!! <br>
 
